<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to raise $1.45 billion in
new cash Thursday by selling a record $10.5 billion in
52-week bills and redeeming $9.06 billion in maturing bills.
   The bills will be dated Aug. 2 and mature on Aug. 1, 1991.
