<HL>
   Financing Business:
   Novell Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
07/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   NOVL
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   NOVELL Inc., a Provo, Utah, maker of software products for
computer networks, said it plans to call for redemption on
Aug. 24 all of its 7 1/4% convertible subordinated
debentures, due 2013, with an aggregate principal amount of
$52 million outstanding. Prior to the close of business on
Aug. 24, holders may convert the debentures into Novell
common at a price of $36 a share. In national
over-the-counter trading Friday, Novell closed at $50.75,
down $3.50.
</LP>
