900723-0013.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Who's News:
   Southeast Banking Corp.
</HL>
<DATE>
07/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   STB WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   SOUTHEAST BANKING Corp. (Miami) -- Douglas E. Ebert,
formerly a sector executive vice president at the
Manufacturers Hanover Trust Co. unit of Manufacturers Hanover
Corp., was named president and chief operating officer of
this bank holding company, succeeding John Porta, who
resigned in March.
</LP>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>
WSJ900723-0012
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900723-0012.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Who's News:
   Langer Biomechanics Group Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
07/23/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   GAIT WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   LANGER BIOMECHANICS GROUP Inc. (Deer Park, N.Y.) -- Paul
S. Langer, 34 years old, chief operating officer of this
maker of medical and health products, was named to the
additional post of president. He succeeds his father, Sheldon
Langer, 66-year-old founder and a podiatrist, who remains
chairman and chief executive officer. Paul Langer's former
post of executive vice president, operations, won't be
filled; he also was president of the orthotics division, a
post that was eliminated. Separately, Jason M. Kraus, 33,
previously vice president, marketing, was named senior vice
president, marketing.
</LP>
